cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper deals with optimization techniques for segmentation and vision problems, which are typically studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The method proposed in the paper involves decomposing the problem into sub-problems, which can be solved in parallel, and updating consistency variables, which are common techniques in distributed computing (cs.DC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper reports experiments on image segmentation, which is a common application of multimedia (cs.MM) research.
